<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He's been forced to postpone his anticipated tour once again.</p>

<p>But Harry Styles is keeping busy despite the news as he filmed the new music video for his latest single Golden which saw him run at full pelt along the Amalfi Coast on Sunday.</p>

<p>The One Direction star, 26, looked dapper as he wore an oversized white shirt that was only partly buttoned-up shirt that showed off his hunky torso underneath.</p>

<p>Going for it! Harry Styles ran at full speed along the Amalfi Coast while in an oversized white shirt and shorts as he filmed the music video for new single Golden on Sunday</p>

<p>The singer completed his look by wearing a pair of white shorts that had gold racer stripes and pink detailing across the front, and he stepped out in white plimsole trainers.</p>

<p>Harry's brunet locks were styled into a side-swept style and he looked ruggedly handsome while he broke a sweat running as he sported a close-cropped goatee.</p>

<p>Running along the pavement as a camera crew followed in front of him in the back of a red sports car, Harry appeared to be in good spirits as he got to work on the music video.</p>

<p>The crew were seen wearing face masks to keep safe amid the coronavirus crisis, making sure to keep their distance from the star while shooting the new scenes. </p>

